      "message": "\u003e I\u0027m not sure I really even understand this.  \n\nYou do understand, we had this same discussion like 100 times already.\n\n\u003e and why PDI can\u0027t consume \"Name1\" as a property?\n\nD-Bus interfaces have a fixed number of properties.\n\nAnother solution would be to simply put an interface with\nfixed properties `Name1`, `Name2`, `Name3`, ... , `Name17`\n\nand consume that on dbus-sensors side.\nThe unused names would then be empty strings and can be ignored by the client.\n\nThat way we stay D-Bus compatible and the PDI abstraction works.\n\nBut that would require build a representation of what a config record is supposed to look like on D-Bus, which is an idea you rejected previously.",
